68
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:22,830
Then the police showed up at his door.

69
00:03:22,830 --> 00:03:26,300
Well, technically they were just a group of
men in hazmat suits s

70
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:28,840
aying they had to see if he was infected.

71
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:32,150
Obviously, to test if he had the coronavirus,

72
00:03:32,150 --> 00:03:34,490
these men had to break into his home,

73
00:03:34,490 --> 00:03:38,970
and take away his laptop, desktop computer,
and cellphone.

74
00:03:38,970 --> 00:03:41,069
And then they took him to a police station.

75
00:03:41,069 --> 00:03:44,970
As is common procedure for well trained medical
staff.

76
00:03:44,970 --> 00:03:48,680
The police “accused him of taking money
from ‘foreign forces,’

77
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:52,120
and threatened to quarantine him for ‘creating
fear.’”

78
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:57,080
Yeah, somehow I don’t think that’s a quarantine
you’d ever come back from.

79
00:03:57,080 --> 00:04:01,400
Luckily, others quickly spread word of Fang
Bin’s detention online,

80
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:03,069
and he was released.

81
00:04:03,069 --> 00:04:05,220
But beyond citizen journalists,

82
00:04:05,220 --> 00:04:08,750
there are also doctors who’ve spoken out.

83
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:10,240
Dr. Li Wenliang

84
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:14,090
was one of eight doctors detained by Wuhan
police

85
00:04:14,090 --> 00:04:17,540
after he warned other colleagues about the
coronavirus.

86
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:19,750
His mistake?

87
00:04:19,750 --> 00:04:23,500
Speaking the truth while the Communist Party
was trying to cover it up.

88
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,290
Police let him go after he signed a statement

89
00:04:25,290 --> 00:04:28,710
hat he would no longer commit “unlawful
acts.”

90
00:04:28,710 --> 00:04:32,160
Unfortunately, none of that matters now,

91
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:34,430
because he died this week—

92
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:38,000
after contracting the coronavirus he tried
to expose.

93
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:42,000
He leaves behind his pregnant wife and a 5-year-old
child.

94
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,400
But the tragedy doesn’t end there.

95
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:48,000
After initial reports from state-run media
that Dr. Li had died,

96
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:52,160
there was a furious backlash on Chinese social
media.

97
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:55,940
And Dr. Li was suddenly no longer dead.

98
00:04:55,940 --> 00:04:59,000
Instead, the hospital said he was in critical
condition

99
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,919
and on life support.

100
00:05:00,919 --> 00:05:04,460
There were reports that Dr. Li had been put
on life support

101
00:05:04,460 --> 00:05:09,460
hours after he had already passed due to the
backlash.

102
00:05:09,460 --> 00:05:12,700
Hours later, after the hospital finally officially
announced his death,

103
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:14,840
the online anger continued.

104
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:16,560
People posted images like this one,

105
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:19,810
with Dr. Li’s mask replaced by barbed wire.

106
00:05:19,810 --> 00:05:24,530
They used references to Les Mis and Chernobyl
to mourn Dr. Li.

107
00:05:24,530 --> 00:05:28,110
And hashtags like I want freedom of speech.

108
00:05:28,110 --> 00:05:29,860
And after that was censored,

109
00:05:29,860 --> 00:05:32,669
we *demand* freedom of speech.

110
00:05:32,669 --> 00:05:35,760
They even posted protest videos on TikTok.

111
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:37,010
But don’t worry,

112
00:05:37,010 --> 00:05:39,830
the Chinese Communist Party knows how to handle
this.

113
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:42,130
First, “control” the online reaction.

114
00:05:42,130 --> 00:05:46,699
And then, send officials to “investigate”
Dr. Li’s death.

115
00:05:46,699 --> 00:05:50,480
The only question is, who will the scapegoat
be?

116
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:52,699
And it’s not just doctors and citizen journalists

117
00:05:52,699 --> 00:05:54,520
